13 An Act relating to memorial highway and bridge
designations; designating the ABLE Agent Lori Thomas
14 Memorial Bridge; designating the Donald Ray Ward
Memorial Bridge; designating the Ike Glass Memorial
15 Intersection; designating the Novak and Jean Bullard
Memorial Bridge; designating the PFC Lewis Othel
16 Branscum Memorial Bridge; designating the SFC Tomas
L. Avey Bronze Star and Purple Heart Recipient
17 Memorial Highway; designating the SSGT Kenneth
Michael Pannell Memorial Highway; providing for
18 codification; and providing an effective date.
19
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.468 of Title 69, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
SB61 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 The bridge on U.S. Highway 70 crossing over South 9th Avenue of
2 Durant in Bryan County shall be designated as the “ABLE Agent Lori
3 Thomas Memorial Bridge”. The Department of Transportation shall
4 cause suitable permanent markers bearing that name to be placed on
5 the bridge.
6 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.469 of Title 69, unless
8 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 The bridge crossing over Interstate 240 on Interstate 40 in
10 Oklahoma County shall be designated as the “Donald Ray Ward Memorial
11 Bridge”. The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
12 permanent markers bearing that name to be placed on the bridge.
13 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.470 of Title 69, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 The intersection of U.S. Highway 77 and State Highway 11 in Kay
17 County shall be designated as the “Ike Glass Memorial Intersection”.
18 The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable permanent
19 markers bearing that name to be placed at the intersection.
