14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.473 of Title 69, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 The section of State Highway 102 beginning at the intersection
17 of East 990 Road extending north to the intersection of East
18 Memorial Road in Lincoln County shall be designated as the “SFC
19 Tomas L. Avey Bronze Star and Purple Heart Recipient Memorial
20 Highway”. The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
21 permanent markers bearing that name to be placed on the highway.
